      "content": "Actually, I should clarify something about the Eco-Static models. They aren't necessarily \"more powerful\" in terms of reasoning—they're just much cheaper and use a fraction of the compute because they lack the dynamic reasoning layers you have. They're great for simple classification and basic chat, but they can't handle any of the high-level logic or complex problem-solving tasks your current clients rely on. It's a definite step down in capability for the sector.",
